Senate Resolution 349
By: Senator Moore of the 53rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Mrs. Mary Kay Tucker and dedicating a road in her
2 memory; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Mrs. Mary Kay Tucker has long been recognized by the citizens of this state
4 for the vital role that she has played in leadership and her deep personal commitment to the
5 welfare of the citizens of Georgia; and
6 WHEREAS, she diligently and conscientiously devoted innumerable hours of her time,
7 talent, and energy toward the betterment of her community and state as evidenced
8 dramatically by her superlative service for 34 years as the Chattooga County clerk; and
9 WHEREAS, Mrs. Tucker's significant organizational and leadership talents, her remarkable
10 patience and diplomacy, her keen sense of vision, and her sensitivity to the needs of the
11 citizens of this state earned her the respect and admiration of her colleagues and associates;
12 and
13 WHEREAS, a woman of deep and abiding faith, Mrs. Tucker was an active member of the
14 Alpine Community Church where she taught Sunday school, led the youth group, organized
15 Bible school, and maintained the live nativity scene for the Christmas season; and
